StudyPopulation: We present an observational study, including 52 cases (53% male and 47% female) treated by a compassionate use ASC program. The mean age was 45 years and ranged from 24 to 69 years. There were 42 perianal fistulas, 7 rectovaginal fistulas, 1 urethrorectal fistula, 1 sacral fistula and 1 hidradenitis suppurativa. All the cases had previous failed surgeries. Thirteen of fifty-two (25%) of the cases presented fecal incontinence at the moment of enrollment. 5/52 (9,6%) of the cases presented anal stenosis and 11/52 (21%) had a scaring anus.
